<font color="#FF0000">COMPASSIONATE COOKIE!</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 31 18:24:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Okay!  So where's Cookie?  I noticed that the brig was empty..Who let'em out?<br><br>
Never mind!  I struck a trail.. someone with his shoes on the wrong feet.. it had to be Cookie..and I was right(as usual).<br><br>
Observed him forcing old ladies to cross the street at gun point..God!  Did my heart ever swell with pride...there Cookie was.. doing the Boy Scout thing the only way he knew how!  Trying his best to compensate for his crimes against UPS.. I suppose.  (I thought his counting cadence was a little bit of an overkill.. but that's Cookie!)<br>
What made it even more special is..&quot;It's the thought that counts...&quot;  and everybody knows that Marines aren't too big on thoughts.  What a paramount effort!!<br><br>
If I can stop crying long enough..I'm gonna cut three life sentences from his pending brig time.<br><br>
BOCIC<br><br>
P.S.  Darn that Cookie's hide!  He chokes me up worse than a can of ham and lima beans.
